<p><b>WINTER SHELTER DONATIONS</b>. If you are travelling this
summer, consider bringing home the toiletries that are
provided in your hotel rooms. Bring them to Coffee
Hour or to the Parish Office so that they can be used by
the men who stay at the Winter Shelter. Not only are you
keeping a few more plastics out of the garbage, but you
are sharing valuable hygiene products with our overnight
guests. Thank you!</p>
<p><b>OUTREACH SUNDAY</b>. Join representatives from several
of the Cathedral’s Outreach Ministries at Coffee Hour in
Cathedral Hall, today after the 10am Mass. They will be
on hand to share some of the work they are doing in our
community. You may also want to learn more so that
you can become involved!</p>
<p><b>FROM HIROSHIMA TO HOPE</b>. On Monday August 6, Pax
Christi members will attend "From Hiroshima to Hope,”
which honors victims of war and the atomic bombings of
Hiroshima and Nagasaki. This annual event begins at 6
pm near the Bathhouse Theater at Green Lake, 7312
West Green Lake Drive North, and includes music, a
program, and a floating lantern ceremony. Please
consider joining us there. <i>Information</i>, visit
<a target="_bulletin" href="http://www.fromhiroshimatohope.org">www.fromhiroshimatohope.org</a> or call Paul Snow,
206-226-5238.</p>
<p><b>A WEEKLY TIP ON CARING FOR OUR COMMON HOME</b>.
During these warmer summer days, try to use air-conditioning
sparingly. AC uses more energy and
contributes to the accumulation of greenhouse gases in
the atmosphere. It also has been demonstrated to have
negative health effects, particularly for those with
respiratory issues and some chronic conditions.</p>


