<p><b>DO YOUR CHILDREN LOVE TO SING?</b> It’s not too early
to start thinking about Fall membership in the Youth
Music program at St. James! Schola Cantorum is our choir for children grades 3–8 
(girls and boys with unchanged voices), and Jubilate! Young Women’s Ensemble is 
our advanced-level group for girls of high school age. Each ensemble provides 
the music for one Sunday noon Mass per month, and participates in annual 
Readings &amp; Carols, Christmas Eve Vigil Mass, and special liturgies throughout 
the year. Tuition is $80 for the semester beginning in September; full 
scholarships available for those with financial need. <i>Information</i>, contact 
<a href="mailto:youthmusic@stjames-cathedral.org?subject=St James Youth Music Program">
Youth Music Director Stacey Sunde</a>, 206-941-9450.</p>


